</td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#666699" width="100%" valign="top">
	
	<!-- Main Post Body -->
	<table width="100%" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0" border="0">
	<td bgcolor="#4D4D73"><img src="images/posticon.gif" border="0" alt="Old Post"></td><td width="100%" bgcolor="#4D4D73"><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" color="#FFFFFF">
	Posted 09-16-2003 <font color="#FEDE01">12:42 AM</font></font></td>
	</tr>
	<tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#666699" vAlign="TOP">
	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" color="#FFFFFF">Having the good fortune (or is that mis-fortune) of knowing a direct decendant of that great aforementioned gnome Bungle, it brings to memory another found tale (of many ) that I have had the great pleasure? to be a part of.<br />
<br />
One evening, Hoggl; who as we all know, is the direct decendant of Bungle, Jagan; a wood-elf of great fortitude, and myself decided that we should head on over to The Tower of Frozen Shadows, as we were wont to invistigate a missing Sorcerous bowl that Hoggl had unintentionaly misplaced, and as well to check on this Wonderous Axe some spirit is suppose to be handing out to those who deserve it. On the way to the Tower, we stopped and added Grimand; a paladin of the right stature (he's a dwarf), Haggrid; one of them Barbarian warrior types, and Binae; another paladin (and although one of them human woman, still a looker). All of course, great friends and members of good standing in the Guild of The Twilight Avengers. Well, after forming our merry little bunch we proceeded directly to the Tower, of which we got to with no trouble at all.<br />
<br />
Once inside the tower, we made preparations to head on up towards the top this tower where it is rumored this ugly woman keeps this Bowl of Hoggl's hidden, and near to where this spirit is known to frequent. Being that we were pressed for time on this particlular evening, we decided to just make ourselves invisible to all the undead types that make this Tower their home. We invised up and sprinted across the first floor of the Tower to the transport mirror that takes you directly to the next level of this Hidous Undead Infested Tower. We port through no problem to the Second floor of this Tower, also known as The library. Still invisible to the undead, we quickly sprinted to the other side of this Library to, once again another transport mirror. We gather close and whoosh, now we are on the 3rd floor of this Tower. Quickly darting past the statues, and down the halls led us to the transport mirror to the 4th floor. Knowing beforehand that a lot of the creatures on the next level can see those that are invisible to the Undead, we quickly changed our line up of spells and Jagan camouflagued us, thinking to make it a quick sprint past most of the 4th floor area right to that ugly witch that is believed to be holding Hoggl's Sorcerous bowl. But as the (mis)fortune of Bungle goes, this is when Hoggl's decendant decided to lay a visit upon us. Holding the magic key to the magic mirror, our little group (along with our new found friend Bungle) was instantly teleported to the 4th floor. At this time, My ability to see those that were camouflaged left me. Ahh, but knowing the way to our next mirror, I dash off quickly to meet my friends at the next portal. Soon I am near the portal and stop by to check on the final resting place of this ugly Bowl stealing wench, when i realize that, even though I cannot see my friends, niether could I hear there footsteps. It is at this time, that Bungle decides to inform us he had decided to visit our friend Hoggl. I turn and rush back toward the place I had last seen my friends, only to quickly discover, I do not know my way around this Tower as well as I had thought. Becoming confused and disoriented, and hearing the clash of steal and spell casting of my friends, I quickly charge down another hallway to my friends rescue. Now, I wonder, who is changing all these hallways around, since I did not find my friends in this one either. I step back out into the nearest hallway, gain my bearings and run back to the Bowl stealing wench and realize my friends still have not caught up with me. Calming myself down some now, I head out into the hallway, heading back to my friens at the first mirror. Walking past many of the creatures wandering about the halls, being I was still camouflaged to most of them, I figured I would find my friends in no time and be able to assist them in whatever troubles they my have gotten into while I was looking for this Bowl stealing wench. It was at this time, Bungle decided to visit me, personaly. My camouflage spell deserted me, I was halfway between the transporting mirror and back to where my friends should be. By this time my friends realize that I am not there to restore their lives that were quickly dwindling to the ever protective creatures that wander these hallways. Also at this same time, Jagan and I crossed paths. Unfortunately neither of us was alone nor had time to say hello, as both of us had picked up some new enemies along our travels. I quickly followed Jagan back to our other friends just in time to see the Life ebb from Hoggl, followed shortly by Grimand, and then Haggrid. A sad sight to see such great warriors fall. But they fell not in vein, for it allowed Jagan the ever so slight time needed to evac Binae, myself and he away. Knowing full well that my ablilties would bring them back unto life again.<br />
<br />
So now you are thinking all is well. The one who can heal, a strong arm, and one capable of teleporting them about quickly has gotten to safety. In no time the talent of these three would surely bring about a good ending. This is not so. Listen up to the rest of this story, and fully realize what the Curse of Bungle truly means my friend.<br />
<br />
Knowing full well what must be done, Jagan, Binae, and myself quickly gather our wits, and head back to the Tower. We hurriedly invised ourselves to the undead types and darted past those foul creatures on the first floor. We gather at the portal and step onto the second floor Library and quickly dash past all the undead foulness found within, sprinting toward the next portal. Quickly steeping through this portal and another quick dash, left us at the portal to the third floor. Were our friends bodies did still lay. Once again, remembering the foul creatures to be found on the next level, Jagan Camouflaged us from their sight and we stepped through the portal. A great sadness then fell upon us, as we laid eyes on our the fallen friends at our feet. A quick moment of mourning and the grim task of reviving our fallen friends begins. I quickly rescisitate Hoggl, which while doing so, causes both Hoggl and myselft to become visible to the ever so diligent gardians of this floor. But not to worry, Jagan quickly cast camouflage on both Hoggl and myself to ensure we would not be spotted by the creatures on this floor, and then quickly camouflaged himself. This little plan seemed to work so well, we decided to try it yet again on Grimands lifeless body. I cast the Rescisitate spell on Grimand and reunite his lost soul with his body. Jagan once again quickly camouflages us from prying eyes. All is good and well so far. Two of our fallen members have been reunited with their lost corpses, we are camouflaged from the prying eyes of the foul creatures of this floor, and only one more lost soul to reunite. A few moments rest to regain the strength needed to reunite a lost soul with their body and I am ready to Rescisitate the last fallen freinds soul to his body. All is in readiness. I reunite Haggrids lost soul to his body. And, of course once again, Bungle pays us a visit. We are spotted by those ever diligently guarding foul beasts. A battle quickly begins. Grimmand and Haggrid are still weakened by Rescisitate spell haven just been cast on them. Hoggl is not yet to full mana. I myself was low on the mana needed to keep my friends alive after just having Rescisitated three of my friends in succesion and as quickly as I possibly could. Haggrid had not even the time to reunite himself with his sword, we were set upon so quickly . Needless to say this visit from Bungle ended up similiar to the previous visit. Hoggl had once again been seperated from his body. Jagan was barely able to once again Evac Binae, Grimmand, Haggrid and myself to safety.<br />
<br />
At this time, Jagan, Binae, Grimand, Haggrid and myself gathered up the lost soul of Hoggl and headed back unto the Tower, with the full belief that with my abilities, We could easily reuinte Hoggl's lost soul with his body left lying in the tower. A simple task for ones such as us, espcially with the help of our lost friends soul. Or so we thought. Jagan transports us through a mystical portal to the continent of Iceclad. The rest of us, eager to be on our way to finish this gruesome task of reuniting Hoggl's lost soul his body, dash off towards the tower, This time Bungle visists our friend Jagan in the form of a lowly snow derve. Being swift of foot, Jagan continues his mad dash to the tower, ignoring this lowly snow derve. This Snow Derve, not wanting to be ignored , brought a few friends to assist in his and Bungle's visit upon Jagan. By this time, Binae,Grimmand, Haggrid and Hoggl's lost sould gain entrance to the tower. I notice that the the snow derves visit upon Jagan is going badly, and turn around to run and assist Jagan during this visit. I didnt make it back to Jagan in time to help assist in this visit. Jagan, full of anger, and quite upset with his visit from Bungle, informs of his decision to ensure that he is fully prepared for any more visists from Bungle and will not make the trip back to his body until he is fully prepared to do so. Meanwhile, Grimand leaves the safety of the Tower and assists me in the search for Jagan's body, which is located somewhere underwater. Thank goodness for all the diving lessons I have been taking at every available chance. After many minutes of searching, Grimand and I give up hope of every finding Jagan's body. We are forced to ask a very young and niave Necromancer for his assistance. Soon, afterwards, Jagan has his body and is ready to be Reunited. As I prepare the spells needed to reunite a body and lost soul, Hoggl informs Jagan, Grimand, Haggrid and myself that Bungle has shown up once again and brought his Curse with him to visit our little bunch once again. It seems, that while I was reuniting Jagan's lost soul to his body, Bungle stopped and payed a visit to Binae and Hoggl. This visit seems to have left both Hoggl and Binae once again seperated from their bodies. Well, we could take no more. We all openly cursed this Bungle again and again. Openly and very loudly. Those undead creatures within the tower cringed at our curses and our free flowing anger I am sure. Even this lady Paladin laid curses upon Bungle thought put a Lizard Warrior's Lips to shame. <br />
<br />
Wasting no time, Jagan, Grimand, and I marched directly into the Tower to our fallen friends bodies. I quickly Rescisitated the two fallen comrades, (inbetween a few more select curses). Being that the hour was now very late. And also feeling we could handle no more visists from our Acursed friends descendants. We bade each other good night and swiflty departed to our homes of safety. Eagerly awaiting our next chance to get together and explore more of these great continents of the Lands of Norrath.</font></p>
	
